name: NPR
text:
A 37-year-old English translator is running against Belarusian President Alexander Lukashenko after her husband was denied registration as a candidate and jailed.

"I'm tired of being silent. I'm tired of being afraid," she said at a giant rally Thursday.
https://t.co/0wTocmTwQ5

name: NPR
text: RT @Lucian_Kim: "I don't need power, but my husband is behind bars. I've had to hide my children. I'm tired of putting up with it. I'm tired of being silent. I'm tired of being afraid." https://t.co/vQJYrbcne5

text:
The Army is now getting back to large-scale training during the pandemic — with some 4,000 National Guard soldiers recently arriving at Fort Irwin, Calif.

Generals say the troops are regularly monitored for symptoms.
https://t.co/hC0xJ6Yva5

name: NPR
text:
Lockdowns have made it difficult to sell goats in India for Eid. 

But goat dealers are finding creative ways to drum up sales — trying everything from a goat beauty pageant hosted by a TikTok star to WhatsApp orders.
https://t.co/HcE2Uv6ogL

name: NPR
text:
The hospital said it made a humane decision to end treatment. 

But Melissa Hickson says her husband, a quadriplegic who’d contracted COVID-19, was denied life-saving treatment because of his disabilities.  
https://t.co/cbmBRgYHg6

name: NPR
text:
The Negro Leagues began 100 years ago to showcase Black baseball players when they were banned from the big leagues. About 100 players are still alive today.

Now, MLB is planning to honor them with a centennial celebration.
https://t.co/ErJsBbbLHG

name: NPR
text:
CNN legal analyst Jeffrey Toobin's book analyzes President Trump's survival in the face of major investigations.

It also asks whether the magic charm that saw Trump through will suffice for him to survive the pandemic.
https://t.co/RrACeA8maP

name: NPR
text:
While the 2020 Emmy nominations were notable for the number of Black shows and creators — there were no nominations in major categories for Latinx talent.

In avoiding one racial controversy, Emmy voters created another one.
https://t.co/hgntndoROr

name: NPR
text:
Is staying at home giving you pandemic restlessness? A new website lets you gaze out windows from around the world  — without going outside.
https://t.co/aQQHqV9C9T

name: NPR
text:
Harris County, where Houston sits, has the fifth-highest number of confirmed coronavirus cases of any U.S. county. 

"I signed more death certificates last week than in my entire life almost all put together,” one doctor says.
